    "content": "nullManage Appointments with Salesforce Scheduler\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Manage Appointments with Salesforce Scheduler\n Set Up Salesforce Scheduler and Book Appointments\n Get Started with Salesforce Scheduler\n Implementation Resources for Salesforce Scheduler\n Manage Business Information in Salesforce Scheduler\n Manage Availability and Exceptions in Salesforce Scheduler\n Define Rules for Finding Appropriate Service Resources in Salesforce...\n How Salesforce Scheduler Determines Available Time Slots\n Customize Appointment Booking in Salesforce Scheduler\n Configure Appointment Email Notifications with the ICS File\n Enable Users to Create and Manage Appointments in Salesforce Scheduler\n Manage Access to Salesforce Scheduler Flows\n Create a Salesforce Scheduler Email Prompt Template\n Considerations for Group Service Appointments\n Appointment Statuses and Status Categories in Salesforce Scheduler\n Set Up Video Appointments with Amazon Chime\n Considerations for Video Appointments with Amazon Chime\n Assign Video Call User Permission to Service Resources\n Enable Video Calls\n Amazon Account Requirements\n Connect Amazon to Salesforce\n Configure External Video Service\n Create a Named Credential for Virtual Calls\n Create Pages for Virtual Calls on Your Experience Site\n Configure Video Calls\n Add the Video Call Utility Item to the Utility Bar\n Add the My Appointments Micro Calendar Console to the Utility Bar\n Configuration of Email Notifications for Unauthenticated Users\n Create a Record-Triggered Flow\n Get Recipient’s Email Address\n Get Service Resource ID\n Get Service Resource Name\n Update Service Appointment Record\n Create an Apex Class for the Apex Action\n Create an Apex Action to Send Email Notifications\n Set Up Outbound Scheduling\n Create and Manage Outbound Appointments in Salesforce Scheduler\n Set Up Inbound Scheduling\n Create and Manage Inbound Appointments in Salesforce Scheduler\n Guest Service Appointment Management in Salesforce Scheduler\n Share Service Resource Availability by Using an Invitation URL\n Lobby Management\n How Salesforce Scheduler Tracks Appointments\n Embed Salesforce Scheduler Flows into Other Flows\n Show Appointments as Events on Salesforce or External Calendars\n Troubleshoot Issues with Appointment Scheduling\n Extend Salesforce Scheduler Functionality with Salesforce Products...\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nSALESFORCE SCHEDULER\nConfiguration of Email Notifications for Unauthenticated Users\n\nTo send notifications about upcoming video appointments to unauthenticated users, create a Record-Triggered flow on the Service Appointment object. Configure the flow to retrieve the recipient’s email address and the assigned service resource name. Then, update the service appointment record to add the service resource name to a custom field. You can then create an Apex action to send email notifications that use the available Virtual Appointment Email templates.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS\nAvailable in: Lightning Experience.\nAvailable in: Enterprise and Unlimited Editions\nNOTE Always make sure that you provide a valid email address for each unauthenticated user. For more information, see Add a user.\nCreate a Record-Triggered Flow\nCreate a flow on the Service Appointment object so that you can configure email notifications.\nGet Recipient’s Email Address\nRetrieve the recipient’s email address from the lead record.\nGet Service Resource ID\nRetrieve the service resource ID from the Assigned Resource object.\nGet Service Resource Name\nRetrieve the name of the service resource from the service resource ID.\nUpdate Service Appointment Record\nAdd the service resource name to the Comments field of the service appointment. You can customize the flow to add the service resource name to a custom field.\nCreate an Apex Class for the Apex Action\nCreate an Apex class that you can link to the Apex action. The email template name in the Apex class refers to the email templates that are used to send email notifications for video appointments to unauthenticated users. You can rename the template based on your setup.\nCreate an Apex Action to Send Email Notifications\nUse the Apex class to create an Apex action that sends email notifications to unauthenticated users.\nSEE ALSO\nGeneral Email Limits\nSingle email daily limits for messages sent using API methods\nEmail Considerations for Sales Engagement\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
